com.ptc.transformation.filter

Interface XMLFilterEntry

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultXMLFilterEntry, VersionedXMLFilterEntry

    public interface XMLFilterEntry
    An Entry object which will be used to identify a XML file. This can be identified by following parameters 1) Entry name - XML File zip entry present in XMLLookUpTable which is same as XML file name which resides in zip 2) Identity entries - these are XPath and value which are used to search the XML file based on the XML content which uniquely identifies an object

    Supported API: true

    Extendable: false

    • Method Detail

      • getIdentityEntries

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getIdentityEntries()
                                                             throws TransformationException
        Identity entries are Key Value pairs which are OR'ed to do a search on a given XML to filter it. Entries should be prepulated by the Developer who implements their object specific identities. For example WTPart root tag based XML file will be uniquely identified with the key as WTPart/ObjectID/ufid value as value inside the XML file. This information will be consumed by Dependency filters to filter their objects based on this dependency. Value will be populated by Querying XML DB.
        Returns:
        Key Value entry

        Supported API: true
        Throws:
        TransformationException

      • getIndentityKeys

        java.util.Set<java.lang.String> getIndentityKeys()
                                          throws TransformationException
        Identity keys are the Keys which are OR'ed to do a search on a given XML to filter it. Entries should be prepulated by the Developer who implements their object specific identities. For example WTPart root tag based XML file will be uniquely identified with the key as /ObjectID/ufid value as value inside the XML file. This information will be consumed by Dependency filters to filter their objects based on this dependency. Identity keys are nothing but, XPATH identification of elements as per their DTD definition.
        Returns:
        Collection of identifty Keys

        Supported API: true
        Throws:
        TransformationException
